My Meme

This meme shows a famous singer named Drake disagreeing with the spelling magic and agreeing with the spelling of magick. Ive made this meme orginal by adding the black boxes and writing. The motivation of creating this meme was from the way we spell magick while using the package, and how this is diffrent to the way magic is normally spelt.

library(magick)
# Drake photo
drake_photo <- image_read("https://forumcontent.paradoxplaza.com/public/615896/drake_reacomodado_by_taringamemes-da5q8ca.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(300)

#black rectangle
box1 <- image_blank (width = 300, height = 244, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate("Magic", font = "Impact", size = 70, gravity = "center", color = "orange") 
box2 <- image_blank (width = 300, height = 289, color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate("Magick", font = "Impact", size = 70, gravity = "center", color = "orange")
box <- c(box1, box2) %>%
  image_append (stack = TRUE)

# bringing it togther
drake_meme <- image_append(c(drake_photo,box))

drake_meme
#save
image_write(drake_meme,"My_meme.png")

My Animated GIF

This meme shows the stages of emotions a student goes through during there project. My motivation to create this meme was myself. I know for a fact I go through these emotions every time I have a project or assignment and im sure im not the only one. I made this gif orginal by adding my own chosen emojis and words to it.

library(magick)

# vector for the counts
counts <- 1 : 4 %>% as.character()

# photos
chill <- image_read("https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/240/apple/325/smiling-face-with-sunglasses_1f60e.png")%>%
  image_scale(250)
sleepy <- image_read("https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/240/apple/325/sleepy-face_1f62a.png") %>%
  image_scale(250)
stress <- image_read("https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/240/apple/325/grimacing-face_1f62c.png") %>%
  image_scale(250)
calm <- image_read("https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/240/apple/325/face-exhaling_1f62e-200d-1f4a8.png") %>%
  image_scale(250)

# orange background
back_1 <- image_blank(width = 650, height = 400, color = "#FF5733") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Before the Project starts", font = "Impact", size = 50, gravity = "south", color = "#FFFFFF")
back_2 <- image_blank(width = 650, height = 400, color = "#FF5733") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2 days before due date", font = "Impact", size = 50, gravity = "south", color = "#FFFFFF")
back_3 <- image_blank(width = 650, height = 400, color = "#FF5733") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2 hours before due date", font = "Impact", size = 50, gravity = "south", color = "#FFFFFF")
back_4 <- image_blank(width = 650, height = 400, color = "#FF5733") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2 minutes after handing it in", font = "Impact", size = 50, gravity = "south", color = "#FFFFFF")

# bringing it together
frame1 <- image_composite(back_1, chill, gravity = "center") 
frame2 <- image_composite(back_2, sleepy, gravity = "center") 
frame3 <- image_composite(back_3, stress, gravity = "center")
frame4 <- image_composite(back_4, calm, gravity = "center")

#frames in order 
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# animation
animation <- image_morph(frames) %>%
  image_animate(fps = 2)

# save
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
